title: Woman mistakes baggage conveyor belt for walkway at Russian airport, gets carried into luggage system. Video - Hindustan Times
summary:
Elderly woman at a Russian airport mistakenly rode a baggage conveyor belt, disappearing into the luggage area.

Date: January 12, 2025 | Source: Hindustan Times

In a bizarre yet hilarious incident at a Russian airport, an elderly woman mistook a baggage conveyor belt for a passenger walkway, leading to an unexpected journey into the airport’s baggage handling area. The entire episode was captured on security cameras and has since gone viral on social media, sparking a mix of laughter and concern among viewers.

Key Points:

  • The incident occurred while preparing for a flight from Vladikavkaz to Moscow’s Domodedovo Airport.
  • The woman mistook the conveyor belt for a walkway, pushed aside a plastic curtain, and fell onto the belt.
  • She was carried into the baggage handling area before airport staff could react.
  • The footage has raised concerns about airport safety protocols.
No serious injuries were reported, but the incident has raised questions about passenger awareness and staff attentiveness at busy airports.

This amusing yet concerning incident highlights the importance of clear signage and safety protocols at airports to prevent such occurrences in the future.
newTitle: Elderly Woman Mistakenly Rides Baggage Conveyor Belt at Russian Airport
